  "notes": [
    "Executor is the backend-neutral seam: Execute(ctx, Statement) error",
    "GroupExecutor and PhaseGroupExecutor extend Executor for atomic/phase-grouped writes",
    "CanonicalNodeWriter writes in strict phase order: retract -> repo -> dirs -> files -> entities -> entity_containment -> modules -> structural_edges",
    "RetryingExecutor handles transient Neo4j and NornicDB MERGE unique conflicts",
    "ExecuteOnlyExecutor hides GroupExecutor from callers that should not use large atomic groups",
    "OperationCanonicalUpsert is for canonical domain nodes (Workload, File, etc); OperationUpsertNode is for SourceLocalRecord writes",
    "No GraphWrite type exists in this package"
  ]
